ctually like to go back to my original statements on the Senate floor on October 31st and what I said was one I think that discrimination and harassment is never ever okay but where I cross a line between you know where I can protect you as an individual and where I can promote your identity is a very fine line for me to walk right and so my response is I don\'t see a conflict between being able to accept love and validate you as an individual and yet not fully agreeing with how you choose identify yourself sexually it\'s a simple I think understanding here they\'re asking you to promote something that is contrary to your fundamental religious beliefs that is requiring you to worship at the altar of something that you don\'t believe in it\'s as simple as that whether it\'s a proclamation or or what you said on October 30th it\'s as simple as that and my problem with this is this is happening across the board in American society if you are a you try to be no one\'s perfect we all fall down but if you try to live your faith and you believe your your faith as I guess stated in the Bible or whatever you view the Bible to be and it\'s contrary to whatever prevailing norm is at at this point popular then you\'re labeled a hater homophobic transphobic any phobic here what comes to mind and they want to shut you down so that now you you are dehumanized so what they\'re accusing you of they are now doing to you requiring you to resign from you know your various positions have no position on campus and be reviled and for that we\'re supposed to give them like two thumbs up I don\'t understand how that\'s diversity today yeah I mean I can\'t tell you how many times I\'ve been called the f-word person online social media on the Senate floor and I mean other slurs that I just don\'t want to repeat on camera oh and again when you say look I love all people but this just like you don\'t agree with everything I believe in I don\'t agree with everything you believe in but I love all