gret it so will their compadres in the broom I want to get your thoughts on the fact that the White House Correspondents Association of announced it it\'s not going to have a comedian roast the media next year what\'s known as the annual nerd prom and said they\'re gonna have biographer Ron chernow who\'s going to be the featured speaker to put some perspective on today\'s politics in history last year speaker annie trump comedian michelle wolf tweeted this in response she said and I quote the White House Correspondents Association are cowards the media is complicit and I couldn\'t be prouder in quote first of all I\'m not sure they had a comedian last year they had Michelle wolf and she just wasn\'t funny so Sean what\'s your response to the fact that Correspondents Association for the first time in decades has decided that they\'re not going to have that kind of lack I will say lack of political humor going on I you know what here\'s my response I applaud Olivia Knox in the White House Correspondents Association for doing this they want to have a dinner that celebrates the First Amendment and it actually shows that that\'s what their intent is so I applaud them for it because they last year they wanted to have a comedian and they talked about how this comedian michelle wolf would have would conduct herself and talk about the First Amendment and it wasn\'t it was rude it was disgusting and I think for them to at least acknowledge the fact that they want to talk about the First Amendment and have a historian do it I don\'t know what this individual is going to talk about but I think at least their intent is right and I\'ll give him credit for that because last year\'s dinner was disgusting and what I thought was more appalling about the dinner than anything is that they they branded it as about the First Amendment the comedian if that\'s what you call her wasn\'t that and no one in the White House Correspondents from NBC ABC CBS CNN said anything about the way that 