I agent this test was designed to push that and lets you know that yes physically you can handle this you can handle the firearms aspect of it you could handle the defensive tactics aspect of it if you do engage with a perpetrator of some sort of a subject that\'s you\'re after this test for the person who stays in shape and takes care of themselves should not be difficult I go to the gym a few days a week so I figured how hard could it be well the test starts off with 60 seconds of sit-ups slow harder than journalism at 47 in a minute earned me four points next up the 300 meter run a time of forty eight point two seconds added another three points to my total halfway done seven points Supervisory Special Agent as Elle Grigsby says there is one simple key to passing the test train this is this is one portion of the process that you have the answers to the test back to my exam for push-ups similar to the first event the goal is to do as many as possible but in this part of the test there is no time limit just do as many as you can till you can\'t go up anymore way less than I thought only got one point for my 32 FBI approved push-ups putting me at eight points heading into the final step not too far off from jumping from journalists to Special Agent then came the mile and a half run look use that break now with only five minutes rest in between each event I definitely felt the toll of the test so how did i do on the run I lost after dropping two points I ended with a final score of six it looks like I\'m sticking a journalism after all in Phoenix Anthony Torre Cronkite news if you have any interest in looking to become an FBI agent the FBI developed the FBI fit test app to help people get accustomed to the test the app will count your push-ups sit-ups and give you your time to rest that\'s it for Cronkite news tonight thanks for joining us for top arizona stories any time go to cronkitenews.azpbs.org [Music] [Music] support for Arizona PBS comes from viewers like you and from SUV right yes well we not only fixed events but we added a few things built in 4G LTE Wi-Fi apple carplay compatibility at a seven-inch diagonal touchscreen we also painted it whoa it\'s a Chevy this is the Chevy equal [Music] after Charlottesville is your sense that there\'s new energy joining these movements this promo Southers is my clip frontline and ProPublica investigates there\'s video of you launching yourself into that crowd tonight a on Arizona PBS explore new ideas and new worlds here on Arizona PBS a community service of error', 'Cronkite News presents in-depth reporting on border issues, sustainability, education, politics, health, business and justice in Phoenix and across Arizona.', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '25-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-11-21 06:47:48', '2018-11-21 06:47:48', '', 25, 'http://localhost/wordpress/27/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
