(30, 1, '2018-11-21 07:00:16', '2018-11-21 07:00:16', 'ears and serve two tours and the good news is they will have Thanksgiving together and Clemson beat Duke proving my mascot theory once again thanks for joining us everyone have a good Tuesday i\'m dana perino here chef [Music] it\'s noon on the west coast 3 o\'clock at the white house where we\'re waiting to see if President Trump talks to reporters as he leaves for Thanksgiving in Florida the president is standing by Saudi Arabia even after what he calls the unacceptable murder of the columnist Jamal keshavjee the president says we may never know whether Saudi Crown Prince was in on it ah but his intelligence agencies have concluded the prince actually ordered the killing also there\'s word Ivanka Trump broke federal rules by using a private email account for official White House business but her lawyer says this is a lot different than what Hillary Clinton did and a live look at the Dow Wall Street on track to wipe out all of its gains for the entire year and breaking news now on Fox News Channel do not eat romaine lettuce anywhere if you have it throw it away if it\'s served to you do not consume it this is a brand new warning from the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention out in the last five minutes reporting begins now breaking news Shepard Smith reporting live from the Fox News deck President Trump stands with Saudi Arabia after the American intelligence community concluded that the Saudi Crown Prince ordered the murder of The Washington Post journalist Jamal keshavjee today the president insulted the murder victim and sided with the Saudis who said our CIA is wrong a live look at the White House where President Trump will have an opportunity to address reporters at any moment now after the statement he issued earlier today we now know that the Saudi hit squad tortured and killed Jamal Khashoggi inside the Saudi consulate in Turkey yet in his lengthy missive riddled with presidential exclamation points mr. Trump wrote today in part we may never know all the facts surrounding the murder of - jamol keshavjee in any case our relationship with the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia the president said that maybe the Saudi Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman knew about the murder or maybe he didn\'t yet the CIA has concluded not only that he knew but that he ordered the brutal killing lawmakers are putting pressure on the White House to punish the Saudis both Republicans and Democrats and US allies are doing the same so the President may not have the last say we\'re waiting for the full report from the CIA but today the president got a head of his intelligence agencies in essence for now it doesn\'t matter what Intel says we\'re standing with the Saudi Kingdom John Roberts reporting live from the White House and we expected the president may stop and talk with the assembled media outside the South portico as he departs from mar-a-lago this afternoon I don\'t imagine he would leave for Thanksgiving chef without a few parting words and he\'ll certainly be asked some questions about his statement regarding Jamal khashoggi which appears to side with the us-saudi relationship rather than what we\'re hearing about the substance of Jamal khashoggi shmurda the president saying in a statement quote King Salman and Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman vigorously deny any knowledge of the planning or execution of the murder of mr. khashoggi our intelligence agencies continue to assess all the information but it could very well be that the crown prince had knowledge of this tragic event maybe he did and maybe he didn\'t if that sounds familiar that\'s exactly what he told Chris Wallace last Friday in an interview in the statement the president said he didn\'t want to risk the relationship with Saudi Arabia hundreds of billions of dollars in military and commercial deals at stake pointing out that 17 Saudis involved in the murder have already been sanctioned by the United States the Secretary of State in the last hour backing up the president saying it\'s a mean and nasty world out there and the president needs to have relationships with countries like Saudi Arabia the president also raised questions about khashoggi himself though going some distance to impugn khashoggi z\' reputation writing quote representatives of Saudi Arabia say that Jamal could show you was quote an enemy of the state and a member of the Muslim Brotherhood but the president going on to say my decision is in no way based on that this is an unacceptable and horrible crime but he put the information out there in an official presidential statement the president in that statement chef also recognizing that Congress is likely going to do its own investigation and may have some recommendations for him the president saying he will look at those recommendations quote but only if they are consistent with the absolute security and safety of America the president also saying that Saudi Arabia remains quote a great ally chef John Roberts reporting from the White House Ivanka Trump while a government employee as assistant to the president sent hundreds of emails to government officials from a personal account even after her father spent many months attacking Hillary Clinton about private emails that\'s according to the reporting of the Washington Post the paper reports the first daughter and presidential adviser used her personal email to contact White House aides and cabinet members and others and that when asked about it she said she was unaware of the rules again even though her father made Hillary Clinton\'s emails a driving force in his campaign he called for Hillary Clinton to be put in jail again and again of course there are differences in these two cases they are numerous Ivanka Trump is not accused of using a private email server she\'s not accused of deleting any emails she\'s not accused of sending classified information but the Washington Post reports the similarities were enough to worry some of the president\'s own advisers the House Oversight Committee under the Republican leadership investigated Hillary Clinton\'s email habits now the incoming chairman of that committee indicated that it will investigate Ivanka Trump back to the chief White House correspondent John Robertson here we go and that is a distinction too that representatives for Ivanka Trump are making today Shep as well the differences between her use of a private email and Hillary Clinton\'s but certainly Ivanka Trump through her representatives is acknowledging that for a time when she first joined the White House last year she continued to use a private email address to do White House business but her attorney Abbey Lowell through spokesman Peter Mary Jane Ian saying quote she did not create a private server in her house or office there was never classified information transmitted the account was never transferred or housed at the Trump Organization no emails were ever deleted and the emails have been retained in the official account in conformity with records preservation rules and laws this first came to light little more than a year ago probably 14 months ago when stories hit about Jared Kushner using a joint family account it\'s i JK family calm to send emails related to White House business at that point Ivanka Trump informed the White House Counsel that she had been using a private that same private email address but not for any classified information she also briefed leaders of Congress on this but Shep a lot of people are sort of raising an eyebrow to say how is it that she was not aware of the rules regarding the use of private email for government business when her father made such a point of it for so many months during the campaign a campaign of which she was a frequent attendee Shep is quite a thing John Roberts thank you when President Trump issued an executive order to change asylum laws in America he essentially said since Congress has enacted I will now a federal judge has countered no you won\'t the judge today blocked the administration from denying asylum to immigrants across the southern border illegally the ruling the obvious Congress makes and changes the laws the president can act as a matter of national security and that\'s exactly what he\'s claiming the caravan the invasion the troops the threat to the nation the judge said no the president cannot simply rewrite immigration laws again John Roberts on a busy day at the White House and the administration is pushing back Shep against that ruling from San Francisco Judge John tiger where the judge came forward and said well you can write all the executive actions you want but you can\'t go against US law and the statement saying quote the rule barring asylum for immigrants who entered the country outside of a port of entry irreconcilably conflicts with the Immigration and Naturalization Act and the expressed intent of Congress whatever the scope of the president\'s authority he may not rewrite the immigration laws to impose a condition that Congress has expressly forbidden the Department of Homeland Security vigorously disagreed with that in a statement this morning saying quote asylum is a discretionary benefit given by the executive branch it is lawful and appropriate that this discretionary benefit not be given to those who violate a lawful and tailored presidential proclamation aimed at controlling immigration in the national interest Judge tiger put in place a nationwide restraining order which will likely mean that a lot of those migrants in the caravan who have been waiting outside of the port of entry in San Ysidro California may make for the nearby hills and try to cross into the border illegally and in that action coincides with an order that was given to the Pentagon from the White House today chef that if Customs and Border Protection officers come under attack the US military backing them up is authorized to use force so we\'ll see which way this goes chef John Roberts thank you the military is now pushing back on reports that the 5800 troops that President Trump sent to the border should be home by Christmas the army commander who oversees troops on the southern border told that to Politico but the US Army responded with an official statement indicating only that it may shift some of its forces to other areas of the border and today some new talk on timing our national security correspondent Jennifer Griffin reporting live from the Pentagon hi chef well as John Roberts just reported a day after a federal judge halted the Trump administration from refusing asylum to immigrants at the border a senior US official confirms to me that the president is preparing to sign off on additional powers for the fifty nine hundred or so US troops that have been sent to the us-mexico border in the past month soon US troops will be allowed to protect the Customs and Border Protection personnel according to officials involved in the planning until now pentagon lawyers had barred US troops from using their weapons for anything other than self-defense at the border Fox was among the first to report earlier this month that the pentagons had rejected an initial DHS request for the US troops to be used in a law enforcement capacity and potentially have contact with migrants that has not changed the signed orders from secretary mattis ordering the troops to the border restricted the troops activity to mostly engineering but now after much back and forth with Defense Department lawyers the White House was informed that the president could grant the troops additional authorities the US troops remain pretty far back from the border I\'m told and would be in a be a line of defense if local and state police and National Guard were somehow overwhelmed yesterday Lieutenant General Jeffrey Buchanan the Army General overseeing the troop deployment said some of the 5900 troops could begin leaving the border as early as this week forcing u.s. army north and u.s. Northern Command to issue the following clarification quote we may shift some forces to other areas of the border to engineering support missions in California and other areas no specific timeline for redeployment has been determined we will provide more details as they become available it\'s not clear how many troops will actually be leaving this week some I\'m told our dentists who were sent as part of the troop deployment I\'m told they will be allowed to go home what I am also told is the orders which expire December 15th are likely to be extended so most of these 5900 US troops chef will not be home for Christmas chef Jennifer Griffin reporting from the Pentagon we\'re still waiting to see if President Trump has any comment before he leaves DC for the Thanksgiving holiday a lot of potential questions from reporters from Ivanka Trump\'s emails to the president stance on Saudi Arabia after the murder of Jamal keshavjee also a new threat for the Northern California area devastated by a massive and deadly wildfire the big fear now with a change in the weather mudslides and the Dow is diving again it\'s now all 592 Points moments ago it was off more than two and a half percent more than 660 points on this session all gains for the year on the markets are now lost a full report is just ahead and we\'re putting together a complete report on the breaking news for the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention it has just announced that no American should eat romaine lettuce there is a new eco lie outbreak the details ahead but if a romaine salad is on your table or in your fridge the CDC says flatly throw it away breaking news and the president is speaking right now to reporters at the White House on the South Lawn this is one of those they record it and then the White House pool plays it back and we play it to you unedited that\'s what\'s coming I\'m told from the White House pool that the topics include his statement on Jamal keshavjee also about Iran the talk is still under way so it\'s probably a few minutes away but we\'ll have this full play back soon and the Fox urgent stocks are now on track to wipe out all of their gains so far this year across all four of the major markets this is a live look at the Dow down 2.2 percent it was down more than two and a half percent more than 206 F I should say 665 points within the last five minutes the word of the day is volatility and the direction of the day is down the Fox Business Network Susan Lee is here man right I hit right off the bat yeah that\'s right so we live in an algorithmic Index trading world and when things unwind they unwind in a hurry the unwind in a big big way as well so you have the stock market down some 600 points at its bottom and the concerns are higher interest rates to come also earnings growth especially for the big tech giants that really rallied so far in 2018 and what does that mean for slowing growth and also trying to trade tensions as well when does that bite into the American wallets the American consumer and eventually the American economy show some big tech stocks are leading the way yeah big tech stocks so we call them the fangs that\'s face all of them all of them and these are a huge market cap in fact they\'re the big drags because they are such an overweight on these markets rights are talking about Facebook Amazon Apple Google as well and Netflix and basically they\'re on bear market territory and what I mean by bear market territory is they\'re down 20 percent from their recent Peaks 20 percent but still if you\'re in Microsoft for example or an Amazon you\'ve made many many double-digit gains so far in 2018 I think there\'s been a reset of expectations how much money are they actually making but when you\'re making 20 30 percent gains and revenue still a pretty darn good year bare market on Apple others to come we\'ll keep a watch Thank You Susan throughout the hour again wiping out all their gains for the year much more to come on that and again the president is speaking right now at the White House we\'ll have the tape turn around also talking I\'ve just been told he\'s just spoken about Ivanka Trump and her emails different tone guessing we\'ll see in a moment stay with us breaking news now on Fox News Channel this is the scene from a mansion in the New York City suburb of Colts Neck New Jersey about 30 miles south of the city fully engulfed officials say there are multiple fatalities but this is more than a house fire the local NBC own television station W NBC here in New York City is reporting that crews found one person shot dead outside that home they also found two other bodies inside the building but at this moment it\'s not clear whether those people died from the fire or whether they were also shot this neighborhood is a very rich one home to many celebrities and wealthy folks who who work here in the city details are sort of sketchy on this except a house fire and someone shot dead in the front yard expect to hear much more on this to come first the fire and now the flood people in Northern California bracing for flash floods and mudslides after the state\'s deadliest and most destructive wildfire on record incinerated entire communities 79 people are now confirmed dead in the small town of Paradise and the surrounding area forecasters say heavy rain is on the way which could help put out the fires but it could also bring even more devastation to a place that already looks like a post-apocalyptic wasteland take a look at this satellite image this is a neighborhood in the town of Paradise from a couple of months ago and look at this that\'s the neighborhood now after the inferno devoured it Claudia Cowan reporting live from a shelter in Chico Claudia and Shepard thousands of fire evacuees are making the best of things at shelters like this one at a church here in Chico donated supplies are helping about 200 people who for now are staying at the gym here these folks are also getting medical attention and mental health counseling two more sets of human remains were found yesterday increasing the number of deaths from the camp fire to 79 the number of those unaccounted for has dropped to about 700 but search crews warned some people may never be found due to the intensity of the flames with evacuation orders now being lifted in some areas around Paradise residents are returning to sift through the rubble of what used to be their home the state\'s insurance commissioner says the losses are staggering in 2017 from all the California fires there was 12 point six billion dollars in insured losses and that was only 6800 single-family homes destroyed here we\'re approaching 11,000 single-family homes destroyed so this is a much more deadly much more destructive fire and insured losses are going to be a lot greater Jones says his office is also educating people about how to avoid getting scammed for instance by unlicensed contractors promising a quick home rebuild bottom line this recovery is going to take years and officials say people should be wary of shortcuts because they say it could cost them more in long run and now rain threatens to bring another kind of disaster yes it will clear out this unhealthy air and yes it will put out what is left of the fire but rain will almost certainly hamper ongoing search and recovery efforts and officials are especially concerned Shepard that a heavy downpour could trigger mudslides Claudia Cowan reporting from Chico California ahead more on Fox top story the killing of Jamaal keshavjee lawmakers from the United States and leaders from abroad calling for the president to do something about it and new information on the government warning you should throw out your romaine lettuce immediately and the none of it there\'s food poisoning there\'s an e coli outbreak the CDC\'s warning is brand new and a live look at the White House where the president is still speaking he\'s just spoken on the four-star general