(34, 1, '2018-11-21 07:05:34', '2018-11-21 07:05:34', 'Sport South Africa October 21st one we are fighting against bad luck says Chiefs coach Salinas after man Yama\'s car accident it is a miracle that libo gangman Yama survived his car accident Kaiser Chiefs coach Giovanni Salinas has said while pleading with fate for the club\'s run a bad luck with injuries to end man Yama has been ruled out for six weeks for Chiefs who meet black leopards in Sunday\'s Telkom Knockout last 16 clash at FNB Stadium kickoff 3.30 p.m. with a fractured arm it was remarkable that man Yama only suffered an arm injury pictures of his crumpled BMW with much of its roof collapsed in after the accident returning home from training on the n1 in Johannesburg suggested he could have suffered far worse I saw the pictures of the car and the accident I said it\'s a miracle Salinas said if you see the pictures of the car it\'s unbelievable I can say God thank you dot we are fighting against bad luck but we continue fighting against this bad luck we started this bad luck with Joseph Malenko and the fractured leg to Joseph after that it was Leonardo Castro now libo so please finish Salinas said to chuckles from journalists but in Kaiser Chiefs we have good players so we have solutions we have options in the squad it\'s a pity about Lee Bo because he started playing good football he played an outstanding game in the Mackay of cup one two two zero against Blume Fontaine Celtic but we continued fighting against the bad luck man Yama arriving at amico see at the start of the season having not played in six months for Coney a spear in Turkey had just begun to find signs of match fitness and format Chiefs before his accident malanga has undergone surgery for a leg broken in amico sees three to 0mt and eight win against free state stars at FNB Stadium on August 11th big Colombian centre forward Castro has been out since injuring his ankle in the first half of Chiefs for 2-1 win over Cape Town City at Cape Town Stadium on September 15 I am optimistic about Castro because he\'s been much better this week he trained with the team started to play small sided game Selena said but he\'s more training by himself still cama billiot was being assessed this week ahead of meeting leopards in the Telkom for a back injury he returned with from the 2019 Africa Cup of Nations of Caen qualifying duty in two full games for Zimbabwe against Democratic Republic of Congo to beast and aware out of the Springboks November tour to Britain and France 10 day beast and the wearer will miss the Springboks November tour to Britain and France robbing the squad of their most experienced player for four tough tests the wearer a33 sustained a neck injury against the All Blacks in Pretoria earlier this month meaning he won\'t add to his 107 caps again this year there was a recall for number eight Dwayne vermeulen who missed the rugby championship due to Japanese club commitments la Klug de jager was also recalled after a lengthy injury lay-off that has kept him out of the entire international season and prof. Trevor Nia Khan is back as well coach Rossi erasmus named a preliminary 20 man squad on sunday which will be fleshed out to about 34 players after next weekend\'s Currie Cup final although more names will be added including some of those northern hemisphere based players erasmus has stuck largely to the same names that have played this year interestingly locked Franco mister twas not named on Sunday as he has just joined English club Gloucester whom he has yet to play for he should be included when Erasmus completes the squad announcement next week it is good to welcome back a player of the caliber of Lud he will add experience to a position where we already have some very good competition for places erasmus said dwayne of course will also bring similar valuable experience to the group according to a Rasmussen Bach coaching staff are looking forward to start working again with the players following a short break after the Rugby championship it\'s a tough tour and our preparation time is limited but we have set ourselves some goals and as has been the case the entire season we would like to see the squad contain you to grow as a group and add to our depth with the 2019 Rugby World Cup less than a year away said Erasmus the Springboks opened their tour on Saturday November 3rd at Twickenham in London when they face England for a fourth time this year the Springboks won a three test home series against Eddie Jones men by two to one in June a week later captaincy yuckle Ozzy and his Springbok team mates tackle France at the Stade de France in Paris on 17 November Scotland hosts the Springboks at Murrayfield in Edinburgh before the tour concludes with a visit to the Principality Stadium in Cardiff to play Wales on Saturday November 24th Springbok training squad forwards shock Brits Ludd de Jager Peter Steph du Toit evidence of each Stephen kits Hafsa Youkilis II C Fran\'s Mallard Malcolm marks Trevor Nia con r.g cinnamon Dwayne vermeulen Warren White Lake Beck\'s Damien de Leon day fi we die and teii Andre ester hawazin Elton Yann cheese Jessie Creole Imbros poppy Hendra Pollard Yvonne vans ill three-chip a coach Erik Tinkler explains why he took gesturing mark Malian Bella off the pitch chip a United coach Eric Tinkler would only say that he did what I felt was necessary explaining his first half substitution of Captain Mark Malian Bella in Saturday nights won 2-0 Telkom Knockout loss against Orlando Pirates Tinkler said the reason for Malian villas substitution being replaced by Dane clat in the 42nd minute should have been obvious to anyone viewing the game my yam Villa was taken off after the former pirates winger had angrily responded with a wave of his arm at his coach this followed Tinkler having given left-wing Malian Bella a mouthful for being caught out of position on a Buccaneers attack Tinkler was supposed to be the first coach to attend the post-match press conference but took so long with his team in the change rooms after the game that pirates coach mullet and Cerrito czervik ended up going first instead Tinkler later joined in the same press conference where normally at pirates home matches the coaches go separately you didn\'t see why surely it\'s obvious the coach responded when questioned on why he took ma Villa offer but it\'s an internal matter and that will be dealt with internally but it was more than obvious this is the biggest game on TV this weekend everybody across the country is watching pirates and you can\'t behave that way so I reacted to it I did what I felt was necessary but it will be dealt with internally my yam Villa later took to Twitter to apologize for gesturing at his coach my yam Villa substitution came in a first half where Tinkler was not happy with his team\'s performance overall we had planned to press pirates ship as coach said we expected them to play in a 3-4 - 3 or a 3-5-2 formation which they changed but we have played against other teams who have played in a 4-3-3 so the whole plan was to look to press them and we didn\'t do that in the first half both kirtland cheese and Rose ate game old I mean were looking to press onto their centre backs it was too easy for pirates to get the ball to moose in the oedema and then they started coming at us and turning us and creating little spaces in between the lines which was something we practiced and we allowed that to happen in the first half I thought in that first half we looked like we were playing with fear so obviously we had to make changes at halftime and I thought the second half was a vast improvement we made better decisions on the ball and are pressing was a lot better how we conceded the goal was a bit disappointing being beaten at the near post but the way the team reacted was extremely positive we got into the right areas but players have to understand that in those areas you have less time and we wanted too many touches in those areas but overall the second-half performance was good first half not great Pirates took the lead in a period where the teams were matching each other chance for chance when colum Lambo was fed into space on the right and cut back for substitute vincent peale to finish at the near post for blown celtic coach Steve cam fella draws positives from defeat to Sun downs the continuing uncertainty over the sale of bloom Fontaine Celtic has been disruptive and frustrating to the financially distressed side but coach Steve can fella is preferring to focus on things he can control to ensure that the club succeeds on the pitch Celtic crashed out of the Telkom Knockout after an opening round one 2-0 defeat to Maine Lodi Sun downs at Lucas Marin Stadium in at Aerojet Valley west of Pretoria on Saturday and a philosophical compeller said he has told his players to always remember their obligation to the supporters despite the challenges each one of the players understands that we have an obligation to the supporters and good performances like these against a strong team like Maine Lodi Sun downs our points of references we lost the game but I am happy that we are getting better and getting somewhere as a team under the circumstances that the club finds itself in at the moment Campello said it\'s about focus and control and I know that those are big words focus is everything because you have to control emotions and if I can\'t control my thoughts then I will say the wrong things in any situation no matter how dire it is you can\'t be controlled by emotions if I can\'t control my thoughts then I am going to say wrong things hence I say control is everything and that is what we do ask to reflect on the match compelling echoed Sundowns counterpart p somos Amane sentiments that the game was good to watch and value for money for the attending fans who braved the chilly weather apart from the goal and the result I thought it was a nice match to watch he said it was a sensible game of football and both teams by virtue of being possession based were immediately pressing in a game where two teams were playing counter pressing there was going to be a lot of duels I thought we managed that very well and came out of their press zones the only thing we lacked on the night was the goal while cam fellows suspected that the only goal of the match by Gaston Cyrano in the second half may have been offside he said would take the defeat on the chin if proved otherwise I still want to look at it the goal again he said if it was offside we will take in on the chin and move forward when we played Sun downs in bloom contained before the FIFA break there was also a goal scenario that did not help cause I am proud of how the players played and the only thing that we did not do was to score a goal five how blurred lines cost the Golden Lions in the Currie Cup semi-finals even before kick-off the Golden Lions were up against it in the Currie Cup semi-final they lost 33 to 24 to the Sharks in Durban on Saturday SW is de Bruin the Lions Super Rugby coach and boss of all coaching affairs at the franchise made a beeline for this writer and a former Springbok seated in Kings Parks Media Center de Bruin was keen to share the news that the Golden Lions task had become even tougher after grizzled tied head prop jacobi Audrey Anse was ruled out and that young surgeon Phillies would start the match de Bruin sought to lower expectations of his team against the brutish sharks pack but to be fair the Golden Lions were on the back foot long before their leadership has been in a state of flux the season which impacted the office of their president head coach and even the Currie Cup captaincy which changed hence from raw scrawnier to Marvin ory back to Khurana and then Nick grew de Bruin who had accompanied the team to Durban was seated in the press box while his coaching team took up customary position behind glass inside the coach\'s box when substitutions were called de Bruin would turn to his colleagues and with hand gestures encourage the next move the Golden Lions have had to do things in a roundabout way because of de Bruins involvement with the Springboks he could only spend limited time with the Golden Lions and former strength and conditioning coach yvonne van rui and was curiously appointed to the hot seat de Bruin having to pull the strings by a remote control was hardly ideal on the field to decision-making lines were slightly blurred scrum-half nick groom only recently took over as captain but number 8 warren Whiteley\'s restoration to fitness meant that he was always going to play a leadership role in the heat of battle in Durban he was certainly the one mostly engaged in conversation with the referee Marius Vander West realizin whose performance for the record perhaps explains why he has disappeared off world rugby sought after refereeing panel in the build-up to the match it was explained that groom for the purpose of continuity would wear the and in durban as Whiteley\'s availability for the final should the Golden Lions reach it could not be guaranteed widely spread himself around the park especially in defense as the Golden Lions spent much of the match scrambling as predicted to young fillies and you have to feel for him buckled him a scrum while the Golden Lions were bossed in the collisions they did however stage a remarkable comeback after falling 23 to 3 behind after 41 minutes and got themselves to within 2 points before the Sharks sealed the match in defeat van roy yen pointed to the positives it is obviously a massive challenge playing an away semi-final especially in Durban with the wind pumping like that sent to coach obviously it hurts for the union it was a massive step forward during the season we played 11 to 13 under 21 players we finished the game with between 4 and 6 4 of the type 5 we finished with our u21 obviously the result is disappointing but it is a big step ahead it was a great opportunity for us we\'ve got a young pack of forwards the Sharks handled the pressure well in the last 5 to 10 minutes but I\'m very proud of the guys he was particularly pleased the team did not drop their bundle at 23 2 3 down we always stand for good work ethic honesty and character he said we had a moment for a decision to either lay down or stand up and fight obviously I\'m proud of the guys to stand up and fight six blue Bulls coach pote human wants Super Rugby job blue Bulls coach boat human declared his intention to coach the Bulls in Super Rugby but admitted that it was a decision out of his hands humans blue Bulls lost a thrilling curry Cup semi-final 35 to 32 after extra time against Western Province at Newlands on Saturday but quality of their performance suggested human certainly has the players backing captain Han Roly Ben Berg described human as a father figure further suggesting that if it were up to the players human might get the Super Rugby job the Bulls are still searching for a Super Rugby coach after John Mitchell took up a contract with the rugby Paul Union RFU to be England\'s defense coach under Eddie Jones Mitchell had just completed a year of his Bulls contract human assisted Mitchell in a Super Rugby campaign that saw the Bulls struggled but also showed evidence of a new positive playing style that yielded some good results including a win over the Hurricanes humans said that if he was asked to coach Super Rugby he would keep building on what Mitchell started it will be a real honor to coach the Bulls Super Rugby side human said but that is not for me to decide it is a great bunch of players and we love each other they played for me and I worked for them I treated them like my own kids so it would be an awesome experience and privilege to coach the Super Rugby side it depends who gets the Bulls coaching job in Super Rugby but if I am given the opportunity one will definitely carry on with what Mitchell started John really laid a good platform but if a new coach comes in he will probably want to stamp his own ideas on the team at this stage there is a lot of uncertainty around the Super Rugby job human has already looked at areas the Bulls need to improve for Super Rugby identifying depth at prop as an issue after another difficult day scrumming against Western Province the Bulls though were impressive against the high riding Western Province restricting the defending champions to only two tries after a season in which they scored a try bonus point in every pool match it was nearly enough to get them over the line our defense was awesome and our scrums were much better human said I must compliment loose head prop Trevor neocon he showed why he can play both sides of the scrum and he did really well against province tide head will colu our defense was really good today we missed that one line out and they scored but you can\'t put that down to our defensive structures our high lines work perfectly for us today the guys made their tackles and put them under huge pressure seven long road back to Davis Cup Elite for SI after relegation in Portugal South Africa\'s Road to the newly established Davis Cup Finals tournament suffered a major setback when they were relegated from Euro Africa Group one in Portugal at the weekend the four to zero dropping against Portugal in Lisbon sees si dropped to Euro Africa group two in 2019 which means they are unlikely to make it to the new eighteen team finals until 2021 at the earliest and even that is a long way off without top player Kevin Anderson who has not played Davis Cup for six years si were outgunned on the slowed red clay of the CIF club internacional de futbol in the heart of lisbon people will say we were underdogs going into the tie vs Portugal playing away on clay against a team of top 200 ranked players we were always up against it tennis SI chief executive Richard Glover said I disagree these are just excuses we lost both our Davis Cup ties this year one at home and one away and so the brutal truth is that we deserve to be relegated back to group two when we were promoted last year it did not mean everything was suddenly rosy within tennis in South Africa similarly relegation now does not mean all is doom and gloom I will definitely be reviewing how I could have better supported our 2018 Davis Cup campaign I expect everyone in and around the team to do the same on Friday top singles player Lloyd Harris was smashed 6 to 1 6 to 1 by Pedro Sousa in under an hour to put SI immediately on the back foot in the second rubber NIC Schultz started well he broke his higher ranked opponent Joe al Sousa served in the opening game and was 32 0 up serving when so saw came back strong and broke back to level the match at 1 to 1 Sosa proved his class in beating of fighting Schultz 6 to 3 6 to 2 to give Portugal their second win on the opening day having won just seven games in two matches on the opening day doubles specialist Raven Klaasen teamed up with Rouen Roelofs against Joey Sousa and Gaston Elias they battled to keep si in the time they were eventually beaten 6 - 4 6 - 7 4 6 - to the doubles rubber when gave the hosts an unassailable 3 to 0 lead both team captains agreed to play 1 reverse singles rubber following the doubles si captain Marcos Andris can aim debutante Junior Phillip Henning to do duty for his country who went up against Joey Dominguez Dominguez beat Henning six two four six to zero to give Portugal a four to zero clean sweep victory the conditions were tough out there klaussen said the court certainly was prepared well by the Portuguese to suit their games and with the capacity crowd behind them it made it tough today but we had our chances and felt we were playing well enough to win the rubber but Joey and Gaston were just too strong Aundre ska was left stunned it was a tough loss and I am still trying to understand where we went wrong said on drew Scott I felt we played well but Portugal were just too good and played extremely well and used their home tie advantage to full advantage and credit to them for doing that on paper Portugal are the higher ranked team individually and as a team so it was always going to be a tall order to beat them especially away but I did feel we had a chance and that the South Africans played.', 'we are fighting against bad luck says Chiefs coach Solinas after Manyama\'s car accident It is a miracle that Lebogang Manyama survived his car accident Kaizer Chiefs coach Giovanni Solinas has said while pleading with fate for the clubs run of bad luck with injuries to end.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'we-are-fighting-against-bad-luck-says-chiefs-coach-solinas-after-manyamas-car-accident-it-is-a-miracle-that-lebogang-manyama-survived-his-car-accident-kaizer-chiefs-coach-giovanni', '', '', '2018-11-21 07:05:34', '2018-11-21 07:05:34', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=34', 0, 'post', '', 0),
