(36, 1, '2018-11-21 07:05:34', '2018-11-21 07:05:34', 'Sport South Africa October 21st one we are fighting against bad luck says Chiefs coach Salinas after man Yama\'s car accident it is a miracle that libo gangman Yama survived his car accident Kaiser Chiefs coach Giovanni Salinas has said while pleading with fate for the club\'s run a bad luck with injuries to end man Yama has been ruled out for six weeks for Chiefs who meet black leopards in Sunday\'s Telkom Knockout last 16 clash at FNB Stadium kickoff 3.30 p.m. with a fractured arm it was remarkable that man Yama only suffered an arm injury pictures of his crumpled BMW with much of its roof collapsed in after the accident returning home from training on the n1 in Johannesburg suggested he could have suffered far worse I saw the pictures of the car and the accident I said it\'s a miracle Salinas said if you see the pictures of the car it\'s unbelievable I can say God thank you dot we are fighting against bad luck but we continue fighting against this bad luck we started this bad luck with Joseph Malenko and the fractured leg to Joseph after that it was Leonardo Castro now libo so please finish Salinas said to chuckles from journalists but in Kaiser Chiefs we have good players so we have solutions we have options in the squad it\'s a pity about Lee Bo because he started playing good football he played an outstanding game in the Mackay of cup one two two zero against Blume Fontaine Celtic but we continued fighting against the bad luck man Yama arriving at amico see at the start of the season having not played in six months for Coney a spear in Turkey had just begun to find signs of match fitness and format Chiefs before his accident malanga has undergone surgery for a leg broken in amico sees three to 0mt and eight win against free state stars at FNB Stadium on August 11th big Colombian centre forward Castro has been out since injuring his ankle in the first half of Chiefs for 2-1 win over Cape Town City at Cape Town Stadium on September 15 I am optimistic about Castro because he\'s been much better this week he trained with the team started to play small sided game Selena said but he\'s more training by himself still cama billiot was being assessed this week ahead of meeting leopards in the Telkom for a back injury he returned with from the 2019 Africa Cup of Nations of Caen qualifying duty in two full games for Zimbabwe against Democratic Republic of Congo to beast and aware out of the Springboks November tour to Britain and France 10 day beast and the wearer will miss the Springboks November tour to Britain and France robbing the squad of their most experienced player for four tough tests the wearer a33 sustained a neck injury against the All Blacks in Pretoria earlier this month meaning he won\'t add to his 107 caps again this year there was a recall for number eight Dwayne vermeulen who missed the rugby championship due to Japanese club commitments la Klug de jager was also recalled after a lengthy injury lay-off that has kept him out of the entire international season and prof. Trevor Nia Khan is back as well coach Rossi erasmus named a preliminary 20 man squad on sunday which will be fleshed out to about 34 players after next weekend\'s Currie Cup final although more names will be added including some of those northern hemisphere based players erasmus has stuck largely to the same names that have played this year interestingly locked Franco mister twas not named on Sunday as he has just joined English club Gloucester whom he has yet to play for he should be included when Erasmus completes the squad announcement next week it is good to welcome back a player of the caliber of Lud he will add experience to a position where we already have some very good competition for places erasmus said dwayne of course will also bring similar valuable experience to the group according to a Rasmussen Bach coaching staff are looking forward to start working again with the players following a short break after the Rugby championship it\'s a tough tour and our preparation time is limited but we have set ourselves some goals and as has been the case the entire season we would like to see the squad contain you to grow as a group and add to our depth with the 2019 Rugby World Cup less than a year away said Erasmus the Springboks opened their tour on Saturday November 3rd at Twickenham in London when they face England for a fourth time this year the Springboks won a three test home series against Eddie Jones men by two to one in June a week later captaincy yuckle Ozzy and his Springbok team mates tackle France at the Stade de France in Paris on 17 November Scotland hosts the Springboks at Murrayfield in Edinburgh before the tour concludes with a visit to the Principality Stadium in Cardiff to play Wales on Saturday November 24th Springbok training squad forwards shock Brits Ludd de Jager Peter Steph du Toit evidence of each Stephen kits Hafsa Youkilis II C Fran\'s Mallard Malcolm marks Trevor Nia con r.g cinnamon Dwayne vermeulen Warren White Lake Beck\'s Damien de Leon day fi we die and teii Andre ester hawazin Elton Yann cheese Jessie Creole Imbros poppy Hendra Pollard Yvonne vans ill three-chip a coach Erik Tinkler explains why he took gesturing mark Malian Bella off the pitch chip a United coach Eric Tinkler would only say that he did what I felt was necessary explaining his first half substitution of Captain Mark Malian Bella in Saturday nights won 2-0 Telkom Knockout loss against Orlando Pirates Tinkler said the reason for Malian villas substitution being replaced by Dane clat in the 42nd minute should have been obvious to anyone viewing the game my yam Villa was taken off after the former pirates winger had angrily responded with a wave of his arm at his coach this followed Tinkler having given left-wing Malian Bella a mouthful for being caught out of position on a Buccaneers attack Tinkler was supposed to be the first coach to attend the post-match press conference but took so long with his team in the change rooms after the game that pirates coach mullet and Cerrito czervik ended up going first instead Tinkler later joined in the same press conference where normally at pirates home matches the coaches go separately you didn\'t see why surely it\'s obvious the coach responded when questioned on why he took ma Villa offer but it\'s an internal matter and that will be dealt with internally but it was more than obvious this is the biggest game on TV this weekend everybody across the country is watching pirates and you can\'t behave that way so I reacted to it I did what I felt was necessary but it will be dealt with internally my yam Villa later took to Twitter to apologize for gesturing at his coach my yam Villa substitution came in a first half where Tinkler was not happy with his team\'s performance overall we had planned to press pirates ship as coach said we expected them to play in a 3-4 - 3 or a 3-5-2 formation which they changed but we have played against other teams who have played in a 4-3-3 so the whole plan was to look to press them and we didn\'t do that in the first half both kirtland cheese and Rose ate game old I mean were looking to press onto their centre backs it was too easy for pirates to get the ball to moose in the oedema and then they started coming at us and turning us and creating little spaces in between the lines which was something we practiced and we allowed that to happen in the first half I thought in that first half we looked like we were playing with fear so obviously we had to make changes at halftime and I thought the second half was a vast improvement we made better decisions on the ball and are pressing was a lot better how we conceded the goal was a bit disappointing being beaten at the near post but the way the team reacted was extremely positive we got into the right areas but players have to understand that in those areas you have less time and we wanted too many touches in those areas but overall the second-half performance was good first half not great Pirates took the lead in a period where the teams were matching each other chance for chance when colum Lambo was fed into space on the right and cut back for substitute vincent peale to finish at the near post for blown celtic coach Steve cam fella draws positives from defeat to Sun downs the continuing uncertainty over the sale of bloom Fontaine Celtic has been disruptive and frustrating to the financially distressed side but coach Steve can fella is preferring to focus on things he can control to ensure that the club succeeds on the pitch Celtic crashed out of the Telkom Knockout after an opening round one 2-0 defeat to Maine Lodi Sun downs at Lucas Marin Stadium in at Aerojet Valley west of Pretoria on Saturday and a philosophical compeller said he has told his players to always remember their obligation to the supporters despite the challenges each one of the players understands that we have an obligation to the supporters and good performances like these against a strong team like Maine Lodi Sun downs our points of references we lost the game but I am happy that we are getting better and getting somewhere as a team under the circumstances that the club finds itself in at the moment Campello said it\'s about focus and control and I know that those are big words focus is everything because you have to control emotions and if I can\'t control my thoughts then I will say the wrong things in any situation no matter how dire it is you can\'t be controlled by emotions if I can\'t control my thoughts then I am going to say wrong things hence I say control is everything and that is what we do ask to reflect on the match compelling echoed Sundowns counterpart p somos Amane sentiments that the game was good to watch and value for money for the attending fans who braved the chilly weather apart from the goal and the result I thought it was a nice match to watch he said it was a sensib