re they\'re completing their homework get them to school if there\'s a PTA join the PTA stay engaged with the web sites go to community events or the school events it it\'s pretty pretty easy you just have to kind of look for some of those opportunities yeah you have to take the initiative you do to get involved what I asked you you know the the students probably may not realize how big a deal this is you know one of 349 schools nationwide are you gonna do something special at the school I know there was the award recently you know notification but anything else or is this something that they will not necessarily recognize so much we are going to do something we have worked really hard for this all of us and so we want the students and they we want to invite the community and their parents to come and have a celebration so I\'ve already started talking to some of my parents that love to do play in things like this and we\'re gonna plan some type of celebration soon yes well it is like I said it\'s a it\'s a very big deal and we just are so congratulatory on what you\'ve achieved over there and really hope that it spreads to other schools that we have and we appreciate your time and continued success thank you that\'s outstanding thanks Kim Cunningham a collection of 25 CCSD schools have been selected by the Nevada Department of Education for their outstanding achievement helping students affected by poverty for that reason the state has named them shining star schools that means the schools are high-performing and they also serve a significant percentage of students in poverty in some elementary and middle schools as much as 75% of students qualify for free or reduced price lunch in these cases these are four or five star rated schools under the most recent Nevada school performance framework the 25 schools include 17 Elementary School\'s two middle schools and six high schools we will show you a list of all the shining star schools at the very end of this program making sure all students have access to books not just at school but at home as well that\'s what spread the word Nevada has work to do in Southern Nevada since 2001 during that time the nonprofit organization has distributed 4.7 million books to more than half a million students and those numbers are likely to get larger very soon joining us now is the co-founder of spread the word lisa hobbyhorse Lisa how are you I\'m great how are you so you\'re expanding we are tell me about that well we\'re very excited to announce that we are moving we are expanding to Washoe County so we\'re taking on schools in the Reno Sparks area we will start by our first two adoptions in November and we\'re very excited to be statewide in helping all the children in Nevada right the first thing becomes my mind is you\'re gonna need more books we are gonna need more books yes definitely so you have to get Northern Nevada kind of understanding the concept of what you do have you started them already we have we have two amazing team members up there already in an office and cleaning warehouse and all that now it\'s time to get the word out and get volunteers and get books donated and start just like we did down here 17 years ago very grassroots getting people involved and believing in what we do and helping the children up there okay well that\'s a great that\'s a great thing to do I imagine there are gonna be a couple of challenges when you kind of because although we\'re in the same state a lot of miles in between there is you know so it\'s not just easy hey run these books up to Reno yeah so there\'s some challenges a couple of those yeah for sure we\'re definitely helping to get started up there and we\'re bringing books up and so forth and get it all started but we really hope that within the next couple months rina will sustain itself all those people will start to grab on to the magic of what we\'ve done down here and it\'ll be its own self-sustaining nonprofit up there as well under 