er by the DMV on American Pacific 1065 American Pacific out in Henderson stop by anytime we\'re open fro t every day we\'d love to have their books okay I know you also work with a lot of companies to get volunteers to come in I\'ve done this myself you have to clean the books right then I donated yeah how do you have those opportunities coming up we do we also we always do we have about five cleanings a week that are opportunities for anybody to come join they\'re on our website you can check it out the dates are listed and then you have to just register as a volunteer we\'ll get you in you you pick your spots so that we have a place for you a lot of times we haven\'t turned anybody away but sometimes we have cleaning and 70 people will show up and we\'re not prepared for that so we started doing this RSVP things so we make sure our staffing is adequate for all the people who come to help it\'s fun yeah it\'s fun and you can bring your family sure we take up to eight years old or under you know eight and older so bring your kids and let them get back to the community - we love it sounds great and we wish you success as you expand state way that\'s awesome that\'s good we\'re very excited all right Lisa thanks so much for your time you bet thank you 55 Clark County School District students have been named semi-finalists in the 2019 National Merit Scholarship Program more than 1.6 million students across the country applied to become a National Merit Scholar just last month about 16,000 students out of the 1.6 million were notified they are semi-finalists and those 55 students from CCSD are among that group each student is qualified to be a finalist based on their extensive application academic record participation in school and community activities leadership abilities employment honors and awards the toughest part of all maybe these 55 students won\'t know until February if they are a finalist well here to talk more about the National Merit Scholarship and the number of CCSD students who made the semi-finals is dr. Diane gullet she is deputy superintendent with CCSD and the semi-finalists Erin\'s son from Clark high school welcome to both of you welcome to inside education and congratulations thank you yeah so tell me about this you found out last couple of weeks tell me how that went down yeah we were in class and they called us up to the office and put us into a conference room and told us that we were all qualified as National Merit semi-finalists and everyone was really excited because it\'s an incredible honor for all of for all of us it\'s a huge huge honor so then of course you had to like tell your parents what what did you do next yeah yeah I texted my mom while I was in the room and yeah she was pretty excited too so exactly dr. gullet help us understand for those of us that are not as familiar with the National Merit Scholarship this is something that will allow many of these students to to literally choose where they want to go colleges will be after these students correct if they become a finalist absolutely and as a deputy superintendent as a parent of a National Merit Scholar I know full well that the colleges really seek these students it\'s very prestigious so there\'s opportunities through various scholarships in terms of whether they choose a college scholarship or one of the national merit scholarships so they have lots of choices in many cases we\'re talking about a full-ride scholarship correct there are colleges throughout our country who offer full rides in terms that they provide tuition and expenses so there\'s a really big array of options for them so it depends on where they want to go and then that College will often offer them some additional scholarships as well Wow so as I understand it Aaron you are now in the application phase er semifinal listen all the semi-finalists have to fill out an application includes an essay and what else there\'s also teacher Dacians obviously like personal information and also a resume with the extracurricular activities that you\'ve done throughout high school okay so you\'re the process of filling that out yeah and that will go into the running to see whether you\'re a finalist what\'s the toughest part is it the essay yeah it\'s definitely it\'s definitely the essence why is that so tough well the other parts the application are fairly straightforward like a resume and activities and stuff but the essay is where you really get to show who you are as an applicant and the application readers want to know about things like what\'s your motivation to learn or what experiences you\'ve had or really just anything that makes you unique and sitting there thinking how can I portray myself in a seven hundred word essay that\'s extremely difficult and it becomes a long process of drafting writing editing and peer review until you end up with essay that can really embody who you are and being able to read the essay and kind of see yourself in it is really satisfying but the whole process that I say writing definitely takes a while oh my gosh there\'s a lot of writing on that essay I think is what you\'re trying to say right so 19 dr. gehler 19 CCSD schools are represented with Merit Scholars five semi-finalists however one school Clark high school had I think probably I don\'t know of 75 25 or 25 students what do we say about that amazing absolutely amazing we have incredible talent and we\'re just incredibly proud of the students leadership at Clark high school I\'ve been there I\'ve walked classrooms I\'ve spent time with the leader and I could tell you takes great leadership and teachers to provide access and opportunity for these students to excel these students are very bright and very talented but providing those opportunities so they can have rigorous courses and have choices there so they can seek their path and and shine and and show the whole rest of the country what they know and what they\'re capable of what do you say about this school there\'s something going on - Clark what is it the environment yeah it\'s just like Clark is just kind of an environment that\'s really set up for academic success the students are all extremely driven to learn we have some of the most rigorous gorgeous of courses in the country and we have teachers who are really passionate about what they teach and always willing to help out the students and we also have a staff and administration that\'s always setting up setting us up for success they\'re always willing to help and they\'re always providing us with opportunities to pursue what everybody want to go into after high school that\'s great before we go I want to find out what what are your plans obviously to go to college but you have a field of study and you have a dream job well right now I really like entrepreneurship and I also really like studying math and science so ideally I would like to become an entrepreneur who uses math and science to create disruptive technologies I\'ve done a little bit of both I\'ve done some entrepreneurship with patenting and development and I\'ve also done some research at places like Stony Brook University and the National Institutes of Health and I really really love doing both so I like to mix the two together as for college I don\'t really have a specific place right now I\'m in the middle of the process you have some time you have some time but I just want to go to a good school that will allow me to pursue an education in mathematics and computer science I think you\'re gonna find it Aaron we wish you the absolute most success we can congratulations again dr. gullet thanks for joining us today my pleasure well finally we want to pass along a well-earned congratulations Clark high school Zeeshan Vakeel did very well during the 3rd international history Olympiad held in Berlin Germany recently the kil competed against 224 students representing 20 different countries including 20 different US states and came away with 3 gold to silver and 5 bronze medals the collection of medals helped Deshawn compile one of the most outstanding performances of any student at the competition he earned gold medals in the art history be a quiz tournament on the period of colonization in Africa as well as the history of the Berlin exam big congratulations to Ishaan the kill and we want to thank you for tuning in to insideeducation whether you\'re a student parent staff member or tax payer we all have a stake in the public education system a quick reminder that you can find this episode and past episodes of inside education on the Vegas PBS website that\'s Vegas PBS Oh RG or the Vegas PBS YouTube page as promised we\'ll be back in two weeks with more stories and interviews that take you inside the Clark County School District and we leave you now with the names of all those shining star schools congratulations to them we\'ll see you soon you', 'CCSD and other celebrate Week of Respect, and we look at school and student achievement.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'ccsd-and-other-celebrate-week-of-respect-and-we-look-at-school-and-student-achievement', '', '', '2018-11-21 07:26:04', '2018-11-21 07:26:04', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=61', 0, 'post', '', 0),
