er by the DMV on American Pacific 1065 American Pacific out in Henderson stop by anytime we\'re open fro t every day we\'d love to have their books okay I know you also work with a lot of companies to get volunteers to come in I\'ve done this myself you have to clean the books right then I donated yeah how do you have those opportunities coming up we do we also we always do we have about five cleanings a week that are opportunities for anybody to come join they\'re on our website you can check it out the dates are listed and then you have to just register as a volunteer we\'ll get you in you you pick your spots so that we have a place for you a lot of times we haven\'t turned anybody away but sometimes we have cleaning and 70 people will show up and we\'re not prepared for that so we started doing this RSVP things so we make sure our staffing is adequate for all the people who come to help it\'s fun yeah it\'s fun and you can bring your family sure we take up to eight years old or under you know eight and older so bring your kids and let them get back to the community - we love it sounds great and we wish you success as you expand state way that\'s awesome that\'s good we\'re very excited all right Lisa thanks so much for your time you bet thank you 55 Clark County School District students have been named semi-finalists in the 2019 National Merit Scholarship Program more than 1.6 million students across the country applied to become a National Merit Scholar just last month about 16,000 students out of the 1.6 million were notified they are semi-finalists and those 55 students from CCSD are among that group each student is qualified to be a finalist based on their extensive application academic record participation in school and community activities leadership abilities employment honors and awards the toughest part of all maybe these 55 students won\'t know until February if they are a finalist well here to talk more about the National Merit Scholarship and the numb