missing devastating stories it happened so fast I think that they they would have been in serious trouble in the hills outside Los Angeles also hit by wildfire they\'re already bracing for another disaster floods it\'s a silent killer there\'s not any warning she Brian Fennessy and his team took us above one of the many burn zones when fire burns in the hills it strips them of water absorbing brush and makes the soil hard during the storm all of that flows right into the sprawling massive communities below a month after wildfires raged near Montecito the mudslides that followed were ten times as deadly leaving far fewer rescued that there\'s a greater risk to life through these mud flows and there are actually two these wildland fires AC disaster many communities are living through tragedy everybody is struggling homes were those who escaped rebuilding their lives from the ruins as the search goes on for the missing Miguel Almaguer NBC News Los Angeles turning now for the fires of the west of the deadly nor\'easter blasting the eastern half of the country tonight millions impacted by an early season snowstorm dangerous conditions snarling roads power knocked out in places in schools shut down a wide path of misery from Missouri to New England our Ron Mott has the latest now from st. Louis winter came crashing into fall today harder wipeout right chronic across the country accidents and spinouts and disbelief over melting snow ice and sleet I don\'t like the weather from New York we\'re bridge commuters were at a standstill down to DC where the white house was blanketed in the Midwest snow in Chicago leading to slippery roads if the weather is bad always ask yourself is this trip necessary and in Cincinnati branches snapping under the weight of heavy ice here another crash here and a crash there and here\'s another one mr. powerlines again airports throughout the storm zone seen more than a thousand delays O\'Hare Atlanta Reagan National all contributing to a day of 