ial tells us tonight the Saudi explanation is quote a great work of fiction but the question tonight will the Trump White House accept the Saudi explanation the State Department is calling it a good start but critics say this is just the accused hitmen becoming the fall guys lester richard engel tonight richard thank you felony murder charges have been filed against two elite Navy SEALs and two marine Raiders were allegedly strangling a Green Beret to death in Mali in 2017 NBC News Pentagon correspondent Hans Nichols now on the shocking crime Navy prosecutors say Staff Sergeant Logan Melgar was asleep when four fellow special operators burst into his locked room found him with duct tape and put him in a chokehold that killed him the mission in Mali was to train local forces to fight al-qaeda terrorists but they turned on their own the Navy accuses the two seals and the two marine Raiders of first driving to their house for the duct tape and then killing the 34 year old Green Beret while perpetrating a burglary initially Navy SEAL tonita Dolf claimed he and Melgar were wrestling and SEAL Adam Cranston Mathews joined in one of those SEALs told a witness that he choked him out to get back at Melgar for a perceived slight before are also accused of conspiracy and obstruction of justice for lying to investigators this type of behavior is unacceptable the larger special operation forces should not be judged by the actions of a few the accused faced the potential of life in prison Hans Nichols NBC News new developments tonight after the arrest of stormy Daniels lawyer Michael avenatti on suspicion of domestic violence avenatti defending himself and so is his most famous client Peter Alexander has the new details for us Peter what\'s the latest on all this hey Lester good evening two adult film star stormy Daniels is speaking out tonight about that domestic violence allegation against Michael avenatti saying that she will hire a new lawyer if it proves to be true Daniels calling the allegation very troubling but st. Americans should reserve judgment until the investigation is complete tonight there are still nose details about what allegedly happened it\'s still unclear who the alleged victim is Los Angeles police say a finale was arrested Wednesday suspected of felony domestic violence he\'s vigorously denied the allegation both his ex-wife and his estranged wife of rushed to his defense avenatti of course one of the president\'s most vocal antagonists today suggested on Twitter that the allegation is politically motivated Lester Peter Alexander at the White House Thanks there is late word this evening the Florida Senate race is headed to a manual recount the votes will now be counted by hand and procedure required by state law because of how close the margin is between Rick Scott and Bill Nelson tonight the FDA says it\'s taking drastic action to stop the spread of what it calls a national epidemic a skyrocketing number of teenagers who are vaping using e-cigarettes and the feds say they want to ban menthol cigarettes altogether we get more from NBC\'s Tom Costello in Boulder Colorado school nurse Liz Blackwell is on the frontlines of an exploding cigarette epidemic it\'s having an impact on whether or not they can participate in sports it\'s having an impact on their relationships within their families the problem is nationwide today the FDA said it\'s taking action what\'s at risk is that we\'re going to reverse the dramatic gains that we\'ve seen in recent years in terms of trying to bring down smoking rates among adults and among kids health experts say the fruity flavors in e-cigarettes target teens now the FDA is ordering stores that sell fruity e-cigarettes to physically wall them off from teens and verify every customer is at least 18 it\'s also moving to ban menthol cigarettes and flavored cigars the stats are alarming a stunning 78% increase in East cigarette use among high schoolers in just one year a 48 percent jump amon